content:
CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system that revolutionized web design. Unlike Flexbox (one-dimensional), Grid handles both rows and columns simultaneously.

## Basic Syntax
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-template-rows: auto;
  gap: 16px;
}
```

## Key Properties
- `grid-template-columns` / `grid-template-rows`: Define track sizes
- `grid-gap` / `gap`: Spacing between items
- `grid-area`: Name and place items
- `fr` unit: Fractional unit for flexible sizing

Grid is supported in all modern browsers and is the recommended approach for page-level layouts.
